e heart of a big city and next to The University of Akron, they probably do not need it. I will give them this much, they started as a small church over 50 years ago and now when they get too large, they create new churches (There is one right down the street from me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) instead of trying to find larger and larger buildings. They also have 5 to 6 services every Sunday (Depending if it is the holiday season or not)<br>
